"text":"","code":"add_pkg_file(   desc_file,   pkg_name = NULL,   pkg_description = NULL,   author_name = NULL,   author_email = NULL,   github_url = NULL,   output_dir = NULL,   use_figlet = TRUE,   figlet_font = \"Slant\",   colors = c(\"red\", \"yellow\", \"green\", \"magenta\", \"cyan\", \"yellow\", \"green\", \"white\",     \"magenta\", \"cyan\"),   unicode = TRUE,   verbose = TRUE )"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/add_pkg_file.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Add package file — add_pkg_file","text":"desc_file DESCRIPTION file. Must provided, used extract package information. Using add_pkg_file(\"DESCRIPTION\"), created <pkg_name>-package.R based DESCRIPTION file. want use specific information, author_name author_email, can provide manually. pkg_name Character string, name package. Default NULL, read DESCRIPTION file. pkg_description Character string, short description package. Default NULL, read DESCRIPTION file. author_name Character string, name package author. Default NULL, read DESCRIPTION file. author_email Character string, email package author. Default NULL, read DESCRIPTION file. github_url Character string, GitHub URL package. Default NULL, read DESCRIPTION file constructed based package name. output_dir Character string, directory save package file. Default NULL, specify , 'R/'. use_figlet Logical, whether use figlet ASCII art generation. Default TRUE. figlet_font Character string, figlet font use. Default \"Slant\". colors Character vector, colors use logo elements. unicode Logical, whether use Unicode symbols. Default TRUE. verbose Logical, whether print progress messages. Default TRUE.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/add_pkg_file.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Add package file — add_pkg_file","text":"Creates file specified output directory","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/as_matrix.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Convert sparse matrix into dense matrix — as_matrix","title":"Convert sparse matrix into dense matrix — as_matrix","text":"Convert sparse matrix dense matrix","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/as_matrix.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Convert sparse matrix into dense matrix — as_matrix","text":"","code":"as_matrix(x, parallel = FALSE, sparse = FALSE)"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/as_matrix.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Convert sparse matrix into dense matrix — as_matrix","text":"x matrix. parallel Logical value, default FALSE. Setting parallelize computation RcppParallel::setThreadOptions. sparse Logical value, default FALSE, whether output sparse matrix.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/as_matrix.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Convert sparse matrix into dense matrix — as_matrix","text":"dense sparse matrix","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/as_matrix.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Convert sparse matrix into dense matrix — as_matrix","text":"","code":"m <- simulate_sparse_matrix(   1000, 1000,   decimal = 3 )  system.time(   a <- as.matrix(m) ) #>    user  system elapsed  #>   0.002   0.001   0.003  system.time(   b <- as_matrix(m) ) #>    user  system elapsed  #>   0.001   0.002   0.003  system.time(   c <- as_matrix(m, parallel = TRUE) ) #>    user  system elapsed  #>   0.001   0.003   0.003  system.time(   d <- as_matrix(m, sparse = TRUE) ) #>    user  system elapsed  #>   0.002   0.000   0.002   m[1:5, 1:5] #> 5 x 5 sparse Matrix of class \"dgCMatrix\" #>       col_1 col_2 col_3 col_4 col_5 #> row_1 2.266     .     . .         . #> row_2 .         .     . 2.467     . #> row_3 .         .     . .         . #> row_4 .         .     . .         . #> row_5 .         .     . .         . a[1:5, 1:5] #>       col_1 col_2 col_3 col_4 col_5 #> row_1 2.266     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_2 0.000     0     0 2.467     0 #> row_3 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_4 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_5 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 b[1:5, 1:5] #>       col_1 col_2 col_3 col_4 col_5 #> row_1 2.266     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_2 0.000     0     0 2.467     0 #> row_3 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_4 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_5 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 c[1:5, 1:5] #>       col_1 col_2 col_3 col_4 col_5 #> row_1 2.266     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_2 0.000     0     0 2.467     0 #> row_3 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_4 0.000     0     0 0.000     0 #> row_5 0.000     0     0 0.000     0  identical(a, b) #> [1] TRUE identical(a, c) #> [1] TRUE identical(b, c) #> [1] TRUE identical(a, d) #> [1] TRUE identical(b, d) #> [1] TRUE"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/check_sparsity.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Check sparsity of matrix — check_sparsity","title":"Check sparsity of matrix — check_sparsity","text":"Check sparsity matrix","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/check_sparsity.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Check sparsity of matrix — check_sparsity","text":"","code":"check_sparsity(x)"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/check_sparsity.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Check sparsity of matrix — check_sparsity","text":"x matrix.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/check_sparsity.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Check sparsity of matrix — chec