code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/grapes-ss-grapes.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Value selection operator — %ss%","text":"","code":"NULL %ss% 10 #> [1] 10 5 %ss% 10 #> [1] 5"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/list_figlet_fonts.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"List available figlet fonts — list_figlet_fonts","title":"List available figlet fonts — list_figlet_fonts","text":"List figlet font files available package system.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/list_figlet_fonts.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"List available figlet fonts — list_figlet_fonts","text":"","code":"list_figlet_fonts()"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/list_figlet_fonts.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"List available figlet fonts — list_figlet_fonts","text":"Character vector available font names.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/list_figlet_fonts.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"List available figlet fonts — list_figlet_fonts","text":"","code":"list_figlet_fonts() #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Available figlet fonts: #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14]   Font: Slant"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/log_message.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Print diagnostic message — log_message","title":"Print diagnostic message — log_message","text":"Integrate message printing function cli package, message function. message suppressed suppressMessages.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/log_message.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Print diagnostic message — log_message","text":"","code":"log_message(   ...,   verbose = TRUE,   message_type = c(\"info\", \"success\", \"warning\", \"error\"),   cli_model = TRUE,   timestamp = TRUE,   level = 1,   level_symbol = \"  \" )"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/log_message.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Print diagnostic message — log_message","text":"... Text print. verbose Logical value, default TRUE. Whether print message. message_type Type message, default info. choose one info, success, warning, error. cli_model Logical value, default TRUE. Whether use cli package print message. timestamp Logical value, default TRUE. Whether show current time message. level Integer value, default 1. level message, affects indentation. Level 1 indentation, higher levels add indentation. level_symbol Character value, default \"  \" (two spaces). symbol used indentation level.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/log_message.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Print diagnostic message — log_message","text":"Formated message printed console.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/log_message.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Print diagnostic message — log_message","text":"","code":"log_message(\"Hello, \", \"world!\") #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Hello, world! log_message(\"Hello, world!\", timestamp = FALSE) #> ℹ Hello, world! log_message(\"Hello, \", \"world!\", message_type = \"success\") #> ✔ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Hello, world! log_message(\"Hello, world!\", message_type = \"warning\") #> ! [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Hello, world! suppressMessages(log_message(\"Hello, \", \"world!\")) log_message(\"Hello, world!\", verbose = FALSE) log_message(\"Hello, world!\", level = 2) #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14]   Hello, world! log_message(\"Hello, world!\", level = 3, level_symbol = \"->\") #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] ->->Hello, world!"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/normalization.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Normalize numeric vector — normalization","title":"Normalize numeric vector — normalization","text":"Normalize numeric vector","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/normalization.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Normalize numeric vector — normalization","text":"","code":"normalization(x, method = \"max_min\", na_rm = TRUE, ...)"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/normalization.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Normalize numeric vector — normalization","text":"x Input numeric vector. method Method used normalization. na_rm Whether remove NA values, setting TRUE, using 0 instead. ... Parameters methods.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/normalization.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Normalize numeric vector — normalization","text":"Normalized numeric vector","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/normalization.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Normalize numeric vector — normalization","text":"","code":"nums <- c(runif(2), NA, -runif(2)) nums #> [1]  0.7689241  0.3299883         NA -0.1344190 -0.5893607 normalization(nums, method = \"max_min\") #> [1] 1.0000000 0.6768455 0.4339007 0.3349384 0.0000000 normalization(nums, method = \"maximum\") #> [1]  1.0000000  0.4291559  0.0000000 -0.1748144 -0.7664744 normalization(nums, method = \"sum\") #> [1]  0.42186177  0.18104446  0.00000000 -0.07374751 -0.32334626 normalization(nums, method = \"softmax\") #> [1] 0.53122745 0.22436873 0.11736890 0.09014101 0.03689391 normalization(nums, method = \"z_score\") #> [1]  1.3625453  0.5006459 -0.1473230 -0.4112697 -1.3045985 normalization(nums, method = \"mad\") #> [1]  1.5716685  0.6744908  0.0000000 -0.2747503 -1.2046437 normalization(nums, method = \"unit_vector\") #> [1]  0.7448972  0.3196770  0.0000000 -0.1302188 -0.5709447 normalization(nums, method = \"unit_vector\", na_rm = FALSE) #> [1]  0.7448972  0.3196770         NA -0.1302188 -0.5709447"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/parallelize_fun.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Parallelize a function — parallelize_fun","title":"Parallelize a function — parallelize_fun","text":"Parallelize function","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/parallelize_fun.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Parallelize a function — parallelize_fun","text":"","code":"parallelize_fun(x, fun, cores = 1, export_fun = NULL, verbose = TRUE)"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/parallelize_fun.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Parallelize a function — parallelize_fun","text":"x vector list apply . fun function applied element. cores number cores use parallelization foreach. Default 1. export_fun functions export function workers. verbose Logical value, default TRUE. Whether print progress messages.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/parallelize_fun.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Parallelize a function — parallelize_fun","text":"list computed results","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/parallelize_fun.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Parallelize a function — parallelize_fun","text":"","code":"parallelize_fun(1:3, function(x) x^2) #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Using 1 core #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Elapsed 0.00 sec #> $`1` #> [1] 1 #>  #> $`2` #> [1] 4 #>  #> $`3` #> [1] 9 #>  parallelize_fun(list(1, 2, 3), function(x) x^2) #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Using 1 core #> ℹ [2025-06-13 02:59:14] Elapsed 0.00 sec #> $`1` #> [1] 1 #>  #> $`2` #> [1] 4 #>  #> $`3` #> [1] 9 #>"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/pearson_correlation.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Correlation and covariance calculation for sparse matrix — pearson_correlation","title":"Correlation and covariance calculation for sparse matrix — pearson_correlation","text":"Correlation covariance calculation sparse matrix","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/pearson_correlation.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Correlation and covariance calculation for sparse matrix — pearson_correlation","text":"","code":"pearson_correlation(x, y = NULL)"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/pearson_correlation.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"Correlation and covariance calculation for sparse matrix — pearson_correlation","text":"x Sparse matrix character vector. y Sparse matrix character vector.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/pearson_correlation.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"Correlation and covariance calculation for sparse matrix — pearson_correlation","text":"list covariance correlation matrices.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/pearson_correlation.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"Correlation and covariance calculation for sparse matrix — pearson_correlation","text":"","code":"m1 <- simulate_sparse_matrix(   100, 100 ) m2 <- simulate_sparse_matrix(   100, 100,   sparsity = 0.05 ) a <- pearson_correlation(m1, m2) a$cov[1:5, 1:5] #>       