etermination (\\(R^2\\)) — r_square","text":"coefficient determination (\\(R^2\\))","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/r_square.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"coefficient of determination (\\(R^2\\)) — r_square","text":"","code":"r_square(y_true, y_pred)"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/r_square.html","id":"arguments","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Arguments","title":"coefficient of determination (\\(R^2\\)) — r_square","text":"y_true numeric vector ground truth values. y_pred numeric vector predicted values.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/r_square.html","id":"value","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Value","title":"coefficient of determination (\\(R^2\\)) — r_square","text":"\\(R^2\\) value","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/r_square.html","id":"ref-examples","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Examples","title":"coefficient of determination (\\(R^2\\)) — r_square","text":"","code":"y <- rnorm(100) y_pred <- y + rnorm(100, sd = 0.5) r_square(y, y_pred) #> [1] 0.7681726"},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/simulate_sparse_matrix.html","id":null,"dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Generate a simulated sparse matrix — simulate_sparse_matrix","title":"Generate a simulated sparse matrix — simulate_sparse_matrix","text":"function generates sparse matrix specified number rows columns, given sparsity level, distribution function non-zero values.","code":""},{"path":"https://mengxu98.github.io/thisutils/reference/simulate_sparse_matrix.html","id":"ref-usage","dir":"Reference","previous_headings":"","what":"Usage","title":"Generate a simulated sparse matrix — simulate_sparse_matrix","text":"","code":"simulate_sparse_matrix(   nrow,   ncol,   sparsity = 0.95,   distribution_fun = function(n) stats::rpois(n, lambda = 